    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-03-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-03-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 6,
                                        1890</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>. I have to acknowledge the receipt of
                                your No. 18 of the 10th ultimo, by which I learn that, contrary to
                                the indications of the first “returns” of the late elections in the
                                Hawaiian Islands, the result throughout the islands proves favorable
                                to the “reform party” and the present ministry.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G.
                                Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
